  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (Minimal profile, W-ON-01 trigger)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. The intended use is prediction of absolute hemolysis index for a Class III VAD at Model Risk Level 5, supporting a regulatory submission under 21 CFR Part 870. All 13 ASME V&V 40 credibility factors have been evaluated; seven were formally assessed and six were flagged as epistemic gaps. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification was performed across all boundary-condition inputs. Despite the richness of the prose scope, no structured hasContextOfUse node is linked from this UnitOfAssurance — the use-scope detail lives only in this description and in the bound Requirement and Claim nodes.",
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/synth/req/cou2-vad-hemolysis-mrl5",
  "bindsClaim": "https://uofa.net/synth/claim/cou2-cfd-hemolysis-absolute-prediction",
  "bindsModel": "https://uofa.net/synth/model/fda-generic-centrifugal-pump-cfd-v3",
  "bindsDataset": [
    "https://uofa.net/synth/data/fda-pump-piv-experimental-2018",
    "https://uofa.net/synth/data/fda-pump-hemolysis-bench-2019"
  ],
